talk with somebody,

00:28:19.270 --> 00:28:22.870
and I wanted to
share with them ways

00:28:22.870 --> 00:28:24.370
to get to know your palate.

00:28:24.370 --> 00:28:27.110
And I think that's so powerful.

00:28:27.110 --> 00:28:31.480
So obviously, when you buy my
book, it's based on my palate,

00:28:31.480 --> 00:28:33.650
because all of the recipes,
I've tasted and said,

00:28:33.650 --> 00:28:35.425
yes, I like them.

00:28:35.425 --> 00:28:37.050
But let's say, if
you don't like lemon,

00:28:37.050 --> 00:28:40.460
and I love lemon, then
nine times out of 10,

00:28:40.460 --> 00:28:42.360
you may not like my recipes.

00:28:42.360 --> 00:28:43.630
Or maybe they're too lemon-y.

00:28:43.630 --> 00:28:46.690
Or maybe you try recipes
that are too spicy.

00:28:46.690 --> 00:28:48.490
But just to get to
know your palate.

00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:51.562
So if you have a talk, and
you say to somebody, well,

00:28:51.562 --> 00:28:52.270
what do you like?

00:28:52.270 --> 00:28:53.226
Well, I like sweet.

00:28:53.226 --> 00:28:54.600
And then, you
think, OK, what are

00:28:54.600 --> 00:28:57.250
the sweet things
that you may like?

00:28:57.250 --> 00:29:00.021
And so you have this list,
sweet potatoes, bananas,

00:29:00.021 --> 00:29:01.270
all of these different things.

00:29:01.270 --> 00:29:02.540
Or let's say you like bitter.

00:29:02.540 --> 00:29:04.714
And you have all of these
things that they like,

00:29:04.714 --> 00:29:06.380
and certain things
that they don't like.

00:29:06.380 --> 00:29:10.920
Let's say they don't like turnip
greens because they're bitter.

00:29:10.920 --> 00:29:13.690
So I can tell you how you can
change that into something

00:29:13.690 --> 00:29:17.790
that you may like by adding a
sweet or a component or salt so

00:29:17.790 --> 00:29:18.820
that you will like it.

00:29:18.820 --> 00:29:22.420
So it helps that person
because, I think, sometimes,

00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:26.611
when people try a dish, and
it's made in a certain way

00:29:26.611 --> 00:29:28.110
that they don't
like, they will say,

00:29:28.110 --> 00:29:30.945
oh, I don't like turnip greens.

00:29:30.945 --> 00:29:32.820
But they don't know why
they don't like them.

00:29:32.820 --> 00:29:34.530
Or they'll say they're not good.

00:29:34.530 --> 00:29:37.210
It's not that they're not
good, you don't like them.

00:29:37.210 --> 00:29:38.580
And there's a difference.

00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:40.950
And so often, people
say something isn't good

00:29:40.950 --> 00:29:41.950
when they don't like it.

00:29:41.950 --> 00:29:44.630
But if they understand
their palates,

