00:52:01.995 --> 00:52:08.510
Now how I was taught
to incorporate saffron,

00:52:08.510 --> 00:52:15.130
I take a little bit of
water and a sugar cube.

00:52:15.130 --> 00:52:17.960
And I actually chop
it up with the water

00:52:17.960 --> 00:52:21.080
because the saffron won't
go flying everywhere.

00:52:21.080 --> 00:52:23.650
So I chop it up, and
I bloom the saffron

00:52:23.650 --> 00:52:24.920
in that little bit of water.

00:52:24.920 --> 00:52:27.601
And then I incorporate
it like that.

00:52:27.601 --> 00:52:29.100
How are you-- you
bloom it in water?

00:52:29.100 --> 00:52:30.710
HILLARY BERGH: I do
bloom it in water.

00:52:30.710 --> 00:52:34.479
Often I use dates
instead of sugar.

00:52:34.479 --> 00:52:35.270
CARLA HALL: Oh yes.

00:52:35.270 --> 00:52:35.990
So you grind it?

00:52:35.990 --> 00:52:36.960
You make a little powder?

00:52:36.960 --> 00:52:37.290
HILLARY BERGH: Mhm.

00:52:37.290 --> 00:52:38.050
CARLA HALL: So that's
the whole thing.

00:52:38.050 --> 00:52:40.575
I said chop it, but I
use a mortar and pestle

00:52:40.575 --> 00:52:42.579
with a little sugar
cube and the water.

00:52:42.579 --> 00:52:44.870
And you grind it up so you
have this saffron water that

00:52:44.870 --> 00:52:46.600
gets incorporated into the dish.

00:52:46.600 --> 00:52:47.505
And you use dates.

00:52:47.505 --> 00:52:48.630
HILLARY BERGH: I use dates.

00:52:48.630 --> 00:52:51.180
Just because I tried
not to use to much sugar

00:52:51.180 --> 00:52:54.029
and I try to go a
more natural approach.

00:52:54.029 --> 00:52:56.195
CARLA HALL: Well, in my
head I saw brown sugar cube.

00:52:56.195 --> 00:52:59.810
HILLARY BERGH: Well,
hey, there you go.

00:52:59.810 --> 00:53:00.561
CARLA HALL: I did.

00:53:00.561 --> 00:53:01.768
HILLARY BERGH: I accept that.

00:53:01.768 --> 00:53:02.710
CARLA HALL: Thank you.

00:53:02.710 --> 00:53:04.050
AUDIENCE: So that
